(43, 5, 17, 43, 9, 4, 4, 'worketh hitherto, and I work', 'Work of the Father', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of work, with Jesus indicating his active role in doing the works of God. The phrase ''worketh'' in John 5:17 connects to the urgency of working in John 9:4, highlighting the necessity of fulfilling divine tasks.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 17, 43, 14, 10, 10, 'My Father worketh hitherto, and I work', 'Connection of Divine Work', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between Jesus and the Father in their works. In John 5:17, Jesus states, ''My Father worketh hitherto, and I work,'' which parallels John 14:10, where He explains that ''the Father... he doeth the works.''', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 17, 51, 1, 16, 16, 'My Father worketh hitherto, and I work', 'Connection of Divine Work', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine activity, as both passages emphasize the ongoing work of Jesus and His role in creation. John 5:17 speaks of Jesus working alongside the Father, while Colossians 1:16 attributes all creation to Him.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 17, 46, 12, 6, 6, NULL, 'Divine Work and Operations', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine work, as both passages emphasize God''s active role in the world. Jesus states, ''My Father worketh hitherto, and I work,'' while Paul notes that ''the same God which worketh all in all.''', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 17, 58, 1, 3, 3, 'My Father worketh hitherto, and I work', 'Divine Work and Authority', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine work, as both passages emphasize the active role of Jesus in upholding creation and performing God''s will. The phrase ''My Father worketh hitherto, and I work'' in John 5:17 parallels the depiction of Jesus in Hebrews 1:3 as sustaining all things.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 17, 1, 2, 1, 2, 'worketh hitherto, and I work', 'Work of God and Jesus', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine work. In John 5:17, Jesus states, ''My Father worketh hitherto, and I work,'' paralleling Genesis 2:2 where God ends His work. Both passages emphasize the ongoing nature of God''s work.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 17, 23, 40, 26, 26, 'My Father worketh hitherto, and I work', 'Divine Work and Creation', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine activity in both passages. In John 5:17, Jesus speaks of His work alongside the Father, while Isaiah 40:26 emphasizes God''s creative power and ongoing involvement in the universe.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 18, 43, 10, 30, 30, 'making himself equal with God', 'Equality with God', 'This connection highlights the theme of Jesus'' divine identity. In John 5:18, Jesus is accused of making himself equal with God, while in John 10:30, he explicitly states, ''I and my Father are one.''', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 18, 43, 19, 7, 7, NULL, 'Connection of Claims to Divinity', 'Both passages emphasize the claim of Jesus to be the Son of God, which leads to accusations of blasphemy. In John 5:18, he makes himself equal with God, while in John 19:7, the Jews assert he ought to die for claiming to be the Son of God.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 18, 50, 2, 6, 6, 'making himself equal with God', 'Equality with God', 'This connection highlights the theme of equality with God in both passages. John 5:18 indicates that Jesus made himself ''equal with God,'' while Philippians 2:6 states that he ''thought it not robbery to be equal with God.''', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 18, 66, 22, 1, 1, 'God was his Father', 'Divine Authority and Life', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine authority, as Jesus claims equality with God in John 5:18, while Revelation 22:1 presents the throne of God and the Lamb, indicating a shared divine presence. Both passages emphasize the significance of God''s role in granting life.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 18, 38, 13, 7, 7, 'making himself equal with God', 'Connection Between Shepherd and Equality', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between the shepherd and God. In John, Jesus claims equality with God, while Zechariah refers to the shepherd as ''my fellow,'' suggesting a divine connection.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 18, 40, 12, 5, 5, 'broken the sabbath', 'Sabbath Observance and Authority', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of the sabbath and its observance. John 5:18 highlights the conflict over sabbath laws, while Matthew 12:5 discusses how priests act on the sabbath without blame, suggesting a deeper understanding of authority in interpreting the law.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 18, 66, 21, 22, 23, 'God was his Father', 'Divine Presence and Authority', 'This connection highlights the theme of God''s presence and authority. In John 5:18, Jesus claims equality with God, while Revelation 21:22-23 emphasizes the direct presence of God and the Lamb as the ultimate source of light and guidance.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 19, 43, 12, 49, 49, 'what he seeth the Father do', 'Connection of Divine Authority', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between the Son and the Father, highlighting that the Son acts and speaks based on the Father''s will. This connection illustrates the unity of purpose and action between Jesus and God.', 'theme', 0.713, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 19, 43, 8, 28, 28, NULL, 'Connection of Divine Action', 'Both passages emphasize that Jesus acts in accordance with the Father. This connection highlights the unity of purpose and action between the Father and the Son.', 'theme', 0.6359999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 19, 45, 8, 11, 11, 'what he seeth the Father do', 'Connection of Divine Action', 'This connection highlights the relationship between the actions of the Son and the Spirit. Both passages emphasize the divine power at work, with the Son doing what he sees the Father do and the Spirit raising Jesus from the dead.', 'theme', 0.391, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 19, 42, 21, 15, 15, 'what he seeth the Father do', 'Connection of Divine Empowerment', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine empowerment in both passages. In John 5:19, Jesus emphasizes that he acts in accordance with the Father, while in Luke 21:15, the promise of wisdom and speech is given to believers, suggesting a similar reliance on divine guidance.', 'theme', 0.363, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 19, 1, 1, 1, 1, 'what he seeth the Father do', 'Creation and Divine Action', 'This connection highlights the relationship between the actions of God and the Son. Both passages emphasize the concept of doing things in accordance with the will of the Father, as seen in creation and Jesus'' ministry.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 19, 1, 1, 26, 26, 'what he seeth the Father do', 'Divine Action and Creation', 'This connection highlights the relationship between the actions of the Son and the creative work of God. Both passages emphasize the idea of doing things in accordance with the divine will, as seen in the Son''s actions reflecting what the Father does.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 19, 19, 50, 6, 6, 'the Son can do nothing of himself', 'Divine Action and Judgment', 'This connection highlights the relationship between the actions of the Son and the righteousness of God as judge. Both passages emphasize the divine authority and the alignment of actions with God''s will.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 5, 20, 43, 3, 35, 35, 'the Father loveth the Son', 'Connection of Divine Love', 'Both passages emphasize the Father''s love for the Son, highlighting the intimate relationship between them. The shared phrase ''the Father loveth the Son'' underscores this connection.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
