(43, 5, 29, 42, 14, 14, 14, NULL, 'Resurrection of the Just', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of resurrection, specifically the distinction between those who have done good and those who have done evil. John 5:29 speaks of the resurrection of life for the good, while Luke 14:14 mentions recompense at the resurrection of the just.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
