(43, 7, 53, 19, 76, 5, 5, NULL, 'Connection of Sleep and Departure', 'This connection highlights the theme of departure and rest. In John 7:53, the phrase ''went unto his own house'' suggests a return to a place of rest, while Psalms 76:5 speaks of those who have ''slept their sleep,'' indicating a state of inactivity or rest.', 'theme', 0.307, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
