(43, 8, 40, 19, 37, 12, 12, NULL, 'Plotting Against the Just', 'This connection highlights the theme of wickedness against the righteous. Both passages emphasize the hostility faced by those who speak truth, as seen in the intent to kill in John and the plotting against the just in Psalms.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 40, 19, 37, 32, 32, NULL, 'Connection of Righteous and Wicked', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of the wicked seeking to harm the righteous. In John 8:40, the speaker is targeted for speaking the truth, paralleling Psalms 37:32, where the wicked watch and seek to slay the righteous.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 40, 43, 8, 37, 38, 'which I have heard of God', 'Connection of Truth and Abraham', 'Both passages emphasize the contrast between Jesus and the intentions of those claiming to be Abraham''s descendants. The mention of seeking to kill Jesus in both verses highlights the rejection of his truth, which aligns with the behavior not exhibited by Abraham.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
