(43, 8, 41, 43, 8, 44, 44, 'ye do the deeds of your father', 'Fatherhood and Deeds', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''father'' in relation to actions. In John 8:41, the claim of having God as their father contrasts with John 8:44, where Jesus identifies the devil as their true father based on their deeds.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
