(43, 9, 29, 5, 34, 10, 10, 'we know that God spake unto Moses', 'Connection Between Moses and Prophets', 'Both passages emphasize the unique relationship Moses had with God. John 9:29 refers to Moses as a known figure, while Deuteronomy 34:10 highlights that no prophet arose like him, indicating his distinct role.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 9, 29, 11, 22, 27, 27, 'this fellow', 'Connection of Disregard for Authority', 'This connection highlights the theme of dismissing authority figures. In both passages, the term ''this fellow'' is used to refer to individuals who are not recognized or respected by those in power.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
