(43, 10, 21, 23, 35, 5, 6, 'open the eyes of the blind', 'Healing and Restoration Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the opening of the eyes of the blind, highlighting a theme of healing and restoration. John 10:21 references the ability to open blind eyes, which directly connects to Isaiah 35:5-6''s prophecy of the blind receiving sight.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 21, 40, 11, 5, 5, 'open the eyes of the blind', 'Healing and Miracles Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of healing, specifically the restoration of sight. John 10:21 references the opening of the eyes of the blind, while Matthew 11:5 lists the blind receiving their sight among other miracles.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 21, 2, 8, 19, 19, 'open the eyes of the blind', 'Recognition of Divine Power', 'Both passages emphasize the acknowledgment of divine intervention. In John, the ability to open the eyes of the blind suggests a miraculous act, while in Exodus, the magicians recognize the finger of God as a sign of His power.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 21, 19, 146, 8, 8, 'open the eyes of the blind', 'Opening of the Blind''s Eyes', 'This connection highlights the theme of opening the eyes of the blind in both passages. John 10:21 questions the ability of a devil to perform such a miracle, while Psalms 146:8 attributes this act to the Lord.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 21, 20, 20, 12, 12, 'open the eyes of the blind', 'Connection of Sight and Hearing', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of sight and hearing as gifts from the Lord. John 10:21 refers to the ability to open the eyes of the blind, while Proverbs 20:12 highlights the creation of the seeing eye and hearing ear.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 23, 44, 3, 11, 11, NULL, 'Connection of Solomon''s Porch', 'Both passages emphasize Solomon''s porch as a significant location. In John, Jesus walks there, while in Acts, Peter and John gather with the healed man, indicating its importance in early ministry.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 23, 44, 5, 12, 12, 'in Solomons porch', 'Connection through Solomon''s Porch', 'Both passages emphasize the location of Solomon''s porch, where significant events occur involving Jesus and the apostles. This connection highlights the continuity of divine activity in this sacred space.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 24, 42, 22, 67, 70, 'If thou be the Christ, tell us plainly', 'Recognition of Christ''s Identity', 'Both passages emphasize the question of Jesus'' identity as the Christ. In John, the Jews ask for a clear declaration, while in Luke, the inquiry about being the Christ leads to a profound acknowledgment of his divine role.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 24, 43, 1, 19, 19, NULL, 'Inquiry About Identity', 'Both passages emphasize a questioning of identity. In John 10:24, the Jews ask Jesus if he is the Christ, while in John 1:19, they send priests to inquire about John the Baptist''s identity.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 24, 40, 11, 3, 3, 'If thou be the Christ', 'Questions of Christ''s Identity', 'This connection highlights the theme of questioning Jesus'' identity as the Messiah. Both passages reflect a desire for clarity about whether Jesus is ''the Christ'' or ''he that should come.''', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 24, 43, 8, 25, 25, 'How long dost thou make us to doubt?', 'Identity and Doubt in Jesus'' Ministry', 'Both passages emphasize the question of Jesus'' identity. In John 10:24, the Jews demand clarity about whether Jesus is the Christ, while in John 8:25, they ask, ''Who art thou?'' highlighting their ongoing uncertainty about who he is.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 24, 11, 18, 21, 21, 'How long dost thou make us to doubt', 'Doubt and Decision', 'This connection highlights the theme of indecision in both passages. In John 10:24, the Jews question Jesus about his identity, reflecting their doubt, while in 1 Kings 18:21, Elijah challenges the people to choose between God and Baal, emphasizing the need for a clear decision.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 24, 42, 3, 15, 15, 'If thou be the Christ, tell us plainly.', 'Expectation of the Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the people''s questioning of Christ''s identity. In John, the Jews ask if He is the Christ, while in Luke, the people ponder whether John is the Christ.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 24, 47, 3, 12, 12, 'tell us plainly', 'Plainness of Speech', 'This connection highlights the theme of clarity in communication. In John 10:24, the Jews ask Jesus to speak plainly about His identity, while 2 Corinthians 3:12 emphasizes using great plainness of speech in conveying hope.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 25, 43, 10, 38, 38, 'the works that I do in my Fathers name', 'Connection of Works and Belief', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of Jesus'' works as evidence of his divine authority. In each verse, Jesus invites the listeners to recognize the significance of his actions as a testament to his relationship with the Father.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 25, 43, 8, 58, 58, 'the works that I do in my Fathers name', 'Connection of Divine Authority', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' divine identity and authority. In John 10:25, Jesus refers to His works as a testimony to His divine mission, while in John 8:58, He asserts His existence before Abraham, reinforcing His eternal nature.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 25, 44, 10, 38, 38, 'the works that I do', 'Connection of Jesus'' Works', 'Both passages emphasize the works of Jesus as evidence of his divine authority. John 10:25 mentions that the works bear witness of him, while Acts 10:38 describes Jesus doing good and healing, showcasing God''s presence with him.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 25, 58, 2, 3, 3, 'the works that I do in my Fathers name', 'Witness of Salvation', 'This connection highlights the theme of witness and confirmation of Jesus'' works and teachings. Both passages emphasize the importance of believing in the message and the evidence provided through Jesus'' actions and those who heard him.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 25, 44, 2, 22, 22, 'the works that I do', 'Witness of Jesus'' Miracles', 'Both passages emphasize the validation of Jesus through miraculous works. John highlights that His works bear witness of Him, while Acts affirms that Jesus was approved by God through miracles and signs.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 26, 43, 8, 47, 47, NULL, 'Connection of Belief and Hearing', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between belonging to God and the ability to hear His words. In John 10:26, Jesus states that those who do not believe are not His sheep, while John 8:47 asserts that those of God hear His words. This highlights a thematic link regarding spiritual recognition and identity.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 26, 47, 4, 3, 4, 'ye believe not', 'Connection of Belief and Blindness', 'This connection highlights the theme of belief and its absence. Both passages emphasize that those who do not believe are separated from the truth, with John noting they are ''not of my sheep'' and 2 Corinthians stating they are ''lost'' and blinded.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 26, 43, 6, 65, 65, 'ye believe not, because ye are not of my sheep', 'Connection of Divine Selection', 'Both passages emphasize the idea that belief and coming to Jesus are contingent upon divine selection. John 10:26 indicates that not all believe because they are not among His sheep, while John 6:65 states that coming to Jesus is only possible if it is given by the Father.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 26, 45, 11, 7, 8, 'ye believe not', 'Connection of Belief and Blindness', 'This connection highlights the theme of belief and spiritual blindness. Both passages emphasize the idea that certain individuals do not believe or see due to a divine condition, as seen in ''ye believe not'' and ''the rest were blinded.''', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 26, 62, 4, 6, 6, 'ye are not of my sheep', 'Connection of Belief and Knowledge', 'This connection highlights the distinction between those who belong to God and those who do not. Both passages emphasize that true understanding and belief are linked to being part of God''s flock or community.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 27, 43, 10, 16, 16, 'hear my voice', 'Connection of Sheep and Voice', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of sheep hearing the shepherd''s voice. In John 10:27, the sheep recognize and follow the shepherd, while in John 10:16, other sheep are also expected to hear his voice, indicating unity under one shepherd.', 'theme', 0.7899999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 27, 66, 3, 20, 20, 'hear my voice', 'Connection of Hearing His Voice', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of hearing the voice of Jesus. In John 10:27, the sheep recognize His voice, while Revelation 3:20 invites individuals to hear His voice and respond.', 'theme', 0.643, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 27, 46, 8, 3, 3, 'I know them', 'Connection of Knowing God', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of being known by God. In John 10:27, the sheep are known by the shepherd, while 1 Corinthians 8:3 states that those who love God are known by Him.', 'theme', 0.629, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 27, 43, 10, 3, 4, NULL, 'Connection of Sheep and Voice', 'Both passages emphasize that the sheep hear the shepherd''s voice and follow him. This connection highlights the relationship between the shepherd and his sheep, illustrating recognition and guidance.', 'theme', 0.601, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 27, 58, 3, 7, 7, 'hear my voice', 'Hearing His Voice', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of hearing God''s voice. John 10:27 highlights the relationship between the shepherd and his sheep, while Hebrews 3:7 calls for responsiveness to that voice.', 'theme', 0.5589999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
