(43, 10, 32, 19, 109, 4, 5, 'good works', 'Connection of Adversity and Good Works', 'This connection highlights the theme of being rewarded with evil for good deeds. In both passages, the speaker expresses a sense of betrayal despite their good works or love. This parallel emphasizes the experience of unjust opposition faced by the righteous.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
