(43, 10, 33, 19, 82, 6, 6, 'makest thyself God', 'Divine Identity and Authority', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine identity, as both passages address the concept of being ''gods'' or having a divine nature. In John 10:33, the accusation of blasphemy arises from Jesus claiming equality with God, while Psalms 82:6 refers to humans as ''gods'' in a divine context.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 33, 45, 13, 1, 1, NULL, 'Authority and Divine Power', 'This connection highlights the theme of authority, as both passages address the nature of power and its divine origin. In John 10:33, the assertion of making oneself God challenges human authority, while Romans 13:1 emphasizes that all powers are ordained by God.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
