(43, 10, 33, 11, 21, 10, 10, 'blasphemy', 'Blasphemy and Stoning Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the act of blasphemy leading to stoning. In John 10:33, the accusation of blasphemy is made against Jesus, while 1 Kings 21:10 describes a similar scenario where false witnesses accuse someone of blaspheming God.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 10, 34, 19, 82, 6, 7, 'Ye are gods', 'Connection of Divine Identity', 'Both passages emphasize the phrase ''Ye are gods,'' highlighting a shared theme of divine identity among humans. Additionally, they both address the consequences of this identity, noting mortality in Psalms.', 'quotation', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
